Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine beige-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 179 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 15 Name Ainesidamos
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0896)
